==English==
===Etymology===
Named for Prince Albert, the husband of Queen Victoria.

===Noun===
A chain used to anchor a pocket watch or other [[fob]] to a [[waistcoat]].  With the passing of their use as a functional item, Albert Chains are still used as jewlery, worn in any number of manners.

